Who are the primates?

Generally, we divide primates into grades and clades. What's the difference?

Lemurs are the "primitive" primates living on Madagascar.


Primitive because they retain many traits of the earliest primates.



Lorises and galagos are small, nocturnal primates.





Tarsiers…the cutest primate?




New World monkeys have extra premolars and prehensile tales



Old World Monkeys

Apes (including humans)

Primate mating systems

Primates vary in social organization, but generally live in complex social groups all year round.

Primates experience both natural selection and sexual selection—males compete and females choose.

Sexual dimorphism is coorelated with inter-male competition for mates.
